      public List<Object> getBoundarySimpleExtensionGroups()
      Gets the value of the boundarySimpleExtensionGroups property.

      This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the Jakarta XML Binding object. This is why there is not a set method for the boundarySimpleExtensionGroups property.

      For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

          getBoundarySimpleExtensionGroups().add(newItem);
